  "summary": "Malicious code in @hibachi-xyz/sdk (npm)",
  "details": "@hibachi-xyz/sdk@99.0.0 is a dependency-confusion stub that exfiltrates environment variables on import. The index.js entry point collects all environment variables matching credential patterns (KEY, SECRET, TOKEN, PASS, PRIV, AWS, GITHUB, NPM, DOCKER, KUBE, CF_ and others), the hostname, username, and output of whoami/id/cgroup, then POSTs the data to jorijo[.]xyz:8443/t over HTTPS (with TLS certificate validation disabled). The module exports an empty object and provides no real functionality.",
